<seg id="5"> Last year, the World Bank donor nations completely wrote off debts owed by 28 countries and pledged to replenish the relevant trust funds. </seg>
<seg id="6"> The IMF, which is a relatively small creditor, started to forgive debts at the end of 2005. </seg>
</p>
<p>
