<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060212.0015" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> (Overseas Affairs about China) Developmental Trend of Economic and Trade Relations between China and Myanmar Good, Has Great Potential </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Yangon, February 12 (reporter: Zhang Yunfei). China's Ambassador in Myanmar, Guan Mu, and Economic and Commercial Counselor Tang Hai said in an interview with the agency's reporter, before Myanmar's Prime Minister Soe Win visits China on the 14th, that the economic and trade relations between China and Myanmar have rich content, various forms, mutual benefits and interest, and are jointly developed and in a good status. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> Ambassador Guan Mu said that in recent years, the friendly relationship between China and Myanmar, established on the foundation of the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence as good neighbors, has been consolidated and developed, and exchanges and collaborations in various fields are increasingly developed and further strengthened. The economic and trade relations of the two countries are continuously expanded and strengthened. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> Counselor Tang Hai said that the mutual visits maintained by high-level leaders of the two countries have vigorously promoted development of economic and trade cooperation and relations between the two countries. </seg>
<seg id="5"> There were 33 economic and trade cooperation agreement documents signed by both sides during the period of mutual visits by high-level officials in 2004, and most of them are being implemented and practiced. </seg>
<seg id="6"> He said that the number for 2004 is 1.14 billion USD; that of 2005 is 1.209 billion USD, and within it, China's export is 0.935 billion USD, and import is 0.274 billion USD. </seg>
<seg id="7"> In last year's bilateral trade, the total trade amount between Yunnan in China and Myanmar (contains the border trade) was 0.63 billion USD, and increased 14.6% compared with that of last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="8"> Tang Hai said that Myanmar has become one of the important markets for China's enterprises to develop contracted projects, and major projects contracted with and constructed by China in Myanmar include power stations, bridges, ports, and factories (such as sugar, textile, cement, and paper pulp factories, etc.). </seg>
<seg id="9"> Since China's enterprises conduct projects and business in Myanmar, it has promoted export of various sets of Chinese mechanical and electrical products, and Myanmar has become one of the important markets for export of various sets of Chinese equipments and mechanical and electrical products. </seg>
<seg id="10"> Based on the statistics of China's Customs, in the past five to six years, the export amount of Chinese mechanical and electrical products has been around 45% of the total amount of Chinese exports to Myanmar. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="11"> Counselor Tang also said that since Myanmar has rich resources, China's enterprises have started to invest in resources development projects such as petroleum oil, natural gas, nickel and copper mines, etc.; therefore, the potential for development of economic and trade cooperation and relations between China and Myanmar is very great. </seg>
<seg id="12"> He hopes that China's enterprises have their long-term vision, learn how to avoid risks, carefully make decisions, establish good images for enterprises, and win honors for China by completing projects on time, with quality and quantity guarantees, after winning bids for projects. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="13"> Both Ambassador Guan Mu and Counselor Tang Hai think that it is a big event for Prime Minister Soe Win to formally visit China in this year's bilateral relations, and it is significant for strengthening political mutual trust, promoting bilateral cooperation, and further development of the friendly relations between China and Myanmar as good neighbors. </seg>
<seg id="14"> It is predicted that both sides will sign several economic and trade agreement documents during his visit. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060212.0074" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> World Bank Plans to Remit and Reduce Debts of Poorest Countries </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Moscow, February 11. World Bank President Wolfowitz said in Moscow on the 11th that the World Bank will completely remit the debts of the poorest countries before the middle of this year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> Wolfowitz held talks in Moscow on that day with finance ministers from countries who came to attend the Finance Ministers Meeting of the Group of Eight Nations. </seg>
<seg id="4"> In the statement released after the talks, he said that the World Bank will implement the debt remission and reduction plan by July 1 of this year, and it is completing all of the technical work for it. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5"> Last year, World Bank donor countries completely remitted the debts of 28 countries, and stated that they would add more funds for related trust foundations. </seg>
<seg id="6"> The organization of the International Monetary Fund has a lower amount of credit rights, and it started to reduce and remit debts at the end of 2005. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> In addition, Wolfowitz said that he welcomes the decision made by Russia to remit the debts of 16 African countries. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060213.0045" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> High-Definition TVs Have Gradually Become Mainstream in United States </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, New York, February 12 (reporter: Fan Xiaolin). As the price of high-definition TV is continuously falling and its market is constantly expanding, US TV broadcasting institutions are also eagerly promoting appropriate high definition TV programs. </seg>
<seg id="3"> The just-ended US "Super Bowl," a US type of football game, has become a warm-up competition for US broadcasters to greet the age of high-definition TV. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> As The Financial Times reported a few days ago, the US Congress has recently passed a bill, and regulates that US broadcasters must completely stop broadcasting current analog TV signals and transmit only digital signals by February 17, 2009. </seg>
<seg id="5"> This means that the complete digitalization of TV program broadcasts has gotten a clear schedule. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="6"> The universalization of high definition TV depends not only on consumer TV purchases, but also the making of high definition TV programs by production institutions. </seg>
<seg id="7"> Although digital TV has been mentioned in the past several years, it is still not a reality. </seg>
<seg id="8"> But a turning point in this issue appeared this year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="9"> As the US's Consumer Electronics Association forecasted, the sales amounts of digital TVs will surpass that of traditional TVs in the United States for the first time this year, and 85% of digital TVs are high definition products. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060213.0049" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> Japanese Researchers Have Developed a New Type of Highly Efficient Manmade Kidney </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Tokyo, February 13 (reporter: Qian Zheng). Researchers at Japan's Tokai University have developed a type of manmade biological kidney that can not only function the same as a human kidney for catabolism, but can also keep useful substances in the body. Since it is small in size and easy to transplant, it is hopeful that it will bring good news to patients who have kidney disease with the further development of the study. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> As Japan Economic and Industrial News reported a few days ago, the newly developed manmade biological kidney is composed of two parts. One is the "manmade nephron," which filters metabolites and water in the blood; the other is the "manmade urinary tubules," which extract useful substances such as water and amino acids from the original urine and sends them back into the blood. </seg>
<seg id="4"> Both the "manmade nephron" and "manmade urinary tubules" are made of hollow threads, and the internal walls of the "manmade urinary tubules" are paved with epithelial cells of urinary tubules that have the function of catabolism. </seg>
<seg id="5"> This type of epithelial cells can treat diseases caused by repeated hemodialysis and decompose the causative substance of "dialysis-related denatured starch" into an amino acid, and send it back into the blood. They can also send those substances necessary for the human body such as glucose, vitamins, and minerals back into the blood again. </seg>
<seg id="6"> Previous manmade kidneys depended on the osmosis pressure gap of dialysis to filter metabolites, which cannot totally get rid of them, and does not have the function of making amino acids and other substances return into the blood. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> Researchers used goats to do the manmade kidney transplant experiment, and the inner walls of hollow threads of the manmade kidney are lined with epithelial cells from a hog. </seg>
<seg id="8"> Two weeks later, researchers confirmed that the manmade kidney is able to function. </seg>
<seg id="9"> They are currently developing the manmade biological kidney using human kidney cells, and are about to do clinical studies after verification of its safety. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060213.0054" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> China's Secure Power Production Still Faces Serious Challenges </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 13 (reporter: An Pei). A leader of the State Power Supervision and Control Committee said on the 13th that although the secure power production generally maintained a stable status in 2005, secure power production still faces serious challenges. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> Vice Chairman of the State Power Supervision and Control Committee Shi Yubo said at the Fifth (expanded) Session of the National Secure Power Production Committee that in 2005 China's secure power production was stable in general, and accomplished the task smoothly for power peak usage in the summertime, realized a secure power supply, actively coped with the strikes of natural disasters, and basically assured the secure and stable operation of power systems, greatly reduced equipment accidents in secure power production and general power network accidents, compared with those of last year, and the health level of power equipment was increased. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> But he pointed out that with changes in power supply and demand situations, and that many of the newly established generating sets are put into operation one after another, secure power production will face new challenges. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5"> These challenges include: regional, seasonal, and time interval power shortages still exist; power supply and demand situations in some regions are still tense; since a good mechanism for the price of power and coal has not been formed, supply of power and coal is still quite problematic; at the same time, the falling power and coal quality problem has not been effectively controlled, and will seriously affect stable operations of generating sets; some power network structures are fragile and their equipment is obsolete, which brings risks to systems' safety; frequent occurrences of accidents in power infrastructure construction have not completely changed, and the situation is still serious. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="6"> Shi Yubo said that with the further development of power system reform, many deep-rooted contradictions will be continuously exposed, and how to maintain stability of employee teams and assure a normal production order will be a new issue to face. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> For the secure power production work in 2006, Shi Yubo said that the basic control secure power production work should be further consolidated; an emergency control mechanism for power safety should be established and quickly perfected to strengthen responsive capabilities for emergencies; coordination between power factories and networks should be strengthened; security of big dams should be assured; safety control of power facility constructions should be strengthened to reduce occurrences of personnel injury and death accidents; information delivery work should be continuously strengthened to assure the accurate, timely, and smooth flow of power safety information. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="8"> It has been learned that based on a new power safety control situation, this year the Power Supervision and Control Committee will revise and perfect the issued Temporary Regulations on Accident Investigation of Power Production, and at the same time will continuously issue and execute additional documents about the safety of the hydraulic power station dam and safety protection of the secondary power system this year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="9"> In 2005, the whole of Chinese society used a total power of 2468.9 billion KWh, and increased 13.45% compared with that of last year. </seg>
<seg id="10"> Facing the situation in which power supply and demand is still tense, and the unfavorable status of transportation problems with coal, power, and oil, power enterprises have taken effective measures and strengthened equipment control, and prevented the occurrence of large equipment accidents in national power production in all of last year. </seg>
<seg id="11"> There were 74 power network accidents, which were reduced by 127 compared with those of last year; equipment accidents were 427, which were reduced by 132 compared with those of last year. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060213.0113" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> Minister of South Africa, in China, Says There Are No "Organized" Criminal Activities against Chinese Citizens in South Africa </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 13 (reporters: Wang Jiangang and Hao Yalin). Charge d'Affaires ad interim and Minister of the South African Embassy in China Vusi Bruce Koloane said in an interview with Xinhua News Agency reporters on the 13th that there are no "organized" criminal activities against Chinese citizens in South Africa. </seg>
<seg id="3"> He said at the same time that the South African government will make every effort to "strike against all forms of criminal activities." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> Vusi Bruce Koloane stated that the South African government hopes to "reduce the crime rate to zero," and wants the life and asset securities of every foreigner who works in South Africa to be fully protected by local laws and citizens. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5"> Since 2006, 4 Chinese citizens have been killed, one after another, in South Africa, and the Chinese world has broadly paid attention to it. </seg>
<seg id="6"> China's Foreign Ministry has contacted the South African side about the matter, and warned Chinese citizens who are traveling in South Africa to increase their awareness of their security and protection, and to strengthen unity and caring for each other among overseas Chinese, and to collaborate with the police to jointly strike against criminal activities. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> "We express our sincerest sympathy and condolences to family members of those victims." </seg>
<seg id="8"> Vusi Bruce Koloane said, "We are sorry for this, and we also want the Chinese people to believe that the South African government is carefully investigating every case related to the Chinese." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="9"> As the embassy of South Africa presented, the South African police have successfully broken a case in which Chen Jianqing, a woman came from Fujian, China, was killed on February 5 in South Africa, and have arrested a suspect. </seg>
<seg id="10"> The police are searching for another suspect at present. </seg>
<seg id="11"> As the South African embassy in China disclosed, the suspect, who is charged with the gun death of a Hong Kong businessman in January of this year, has been arrested by the South African police, and the belongings of the victim have been recovered. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="12"> When talking about the possible impacts of the killings of Chinese citizens, Vusi Bruce Koloane thinks that those incidents will "indeed" impact trade, tourism, and exchanges in other fields between the two countries, and produce negative outcomes. But in the long run, those impacts "should not be big." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="13"> As Tourist Attache of the South African embassy Nian Beixi presented, the embassy issued more than 2,000 visas for Chinese to go to South Africa in the first 15 days of this year. </seg>
<seg id="14"> Based on the statistical data of the Chinese government, South Africa had maintained its number one status as China's biggest trade partner in Africa in 2005. </seg>
<seg id="15"> The bilateral trade amount reached 7.27 billion USD, and increased 23% compared with that of last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="16"> However, people in the tourist industry think that the continuous occurrences of killing Chinese citizens in 2004 have apparently affected the number of tourists who visited South Africa. </seg>
<seg id="17"> Based on the statistics of the Sightseeing Bureau of South Africa, there were 20,331 Chinese tourists who visited South Africa in the first half of 2005, which were reduced 14.9% compared with that of last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="18"> There are about 200,000 Chinese who live in South Africa at present, and are scattered everywhere in the towns and villages of South Africa. </seg>
<seg id="19"> Analysts here think that since there are big gaps between the rich and poor in South African society, and a high unemployment rate, guns are spread everywhere, and no death penalty, the crime rate is still high there. </seg>
<seg id="20"> Because many Chinese do not speak English, and they carry cash with them and put cash in their homes, they become easy targets for criminals to attack them for their assets. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060213.0121" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> (Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan) Hong Kong Promotes Occupational English Study and Training </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Hong Kong, February 13. The "Occupational English Campaign" launched by the government of Hong Kong Special Administrative Region made a new plan on the 13th to make more on-the-job people upgrade their English level. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> The plan, named "Studying English Well for Enrichment of Life," includes a series of publicity activities to promote occupational English study and training, and let employers further learn how to help their employees upgrade their English level. </seg>
<seg id="4"> As of now, the plan has funded 25,000 people to complete English training courses, and meet Hong Kong's occupational English requirements related to their job categories. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5"> The Hong Kong "Occupational English Campaign" was launched by the government of the special administrative region in 2000. </seg>
<seg id="6"> One important project of the "Occupational English Campaign" is to provide an assistance plan for occupational English training. </seg>
<seg id="7"> The plan refers to helping employees who need to use English in their work through participating in training and taking designated international business English tests to reach the occupational English level required in their job categories. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060214.0010" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> AIDS Test Will be Free, Voluntary, and Confidential in Hebei </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Shi Jiazhang, February 14 (reporter: Dong Zhiyong). The Health Bureau of Hebei Province issued the Work Solution for Voluntary Consulting AIDS Test in Hebei Province (trial) a few days ago, and clearly stipulated that the AIDS test follows free, voluntary, and confidential principles, and hopes to identify AIDS infectors and patients to the maximum, and to further implement prevention and intervention measures, and the "four free-one care" policy. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> The Solution confirms the working principle for voluntary consulting AIDS testing in Hebei Province: AIDS antibody tests and consultations are free; AIDS antibody tests and consultations are voluntary and of informed consent; AIDS antibody tests and consultations are confidential, and there is no assessment of consulters' related behavior; the legal rights and interest of AIDS virus infectors and patients are protected, and subsequent appropriate services are provided for them. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> The Solution requires that AIDS consultation test sites should be established at convenient places for consulters, and separate rooms should be used for one-on-one consulting in order to protect the consulters' privacy. </seg>
<seg id="5"> Selection of consultants should fully consider individuals' quality, sense of responsibility, knowledge and communication ability, etc. </seg>
<seg id="6"> To protect the privacy of consulters, test forms can be registered with codes or serial numbers. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> The Solution also requires that health administrative units at the county level or above should publish the names and consultation phone numbers of local medical and health institutions responsible for voluntary and free AIDS tests in the major local media, and make it convenient for the masses to know related information. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060214.0047" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> Working Priority of Public Security Ministry Still Focused on Supervision and Investigation on Forcing Confessions by Torture </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 14 (reporter: Meng Na). Deputy Director of the Police Affairs Supervision and Investigation Bureau of the Public Security Ministry Zheng Baigang pointed out when answering foreign reporters' questions in a news conference held by the Public Security Bureau on the 14th, that the so-called "using of methods that are not totally proper to make a crime suspect make a confession" are never allowed in China. </seg>
<seg id="3"> The working priority of the supervision and investigation departments is also to prevent these problems from happening. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> He also pointed out that some international organizations do not have a thorough and correct understanding of the law enforcement status of China's police. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5"> The newest material provided by the Public Security Ministry on the 14th demonstrates that the Case Records Regulation on Implementation of Detention by Public Security Organizations and Regulation on Continuous Interrogation Used by Public Security Organizations issued by the Public Security Ministry in 2002 and 2004, respectively, have better assured local public security units of using detention and interrogation measures according to the law. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="6"> Since 1997, to further promote the "three corrections" (i.e. corrections of forcing confessions by torture, abuse of guns and equipment by the police, and abuse of coercive measures), the public security's police affairs supervision and investigation forces have gone into grass-roots and front law enforcement units including street police stations, police teams, police patrol teams, police traffic teams, and supervision and control sites of public security units, to enforce laws on site. They have investigated law enforcement links publicly that involve citizens' personal security and rights, and made private visits for them in order to look for oversights and errors by law enforcement units, and to remind and warn them to avoid mistakes from the beginning. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> To prevent the occurrence of law enforcement problems from the beginning, police affairs supervision and investigation units have further stretched their law enforcement supervision and investigation antennas, and strengthened the supervision and investigation on law enforcement links including use of subpoena measures, inquiry and interrogation, 110 contact with the police, registered case statistics, handling of properties related to cases, records of information and materials about individuals who were fined, and stolen and hijacked mobile vehicles, etc. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060214.0231" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> (Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan) Sun Yun-suan Dead of Diseases in Taipei </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 15. Taipei News: Sun Yun-suan, who was the Honorary Chair of the Board of the Taiwan Strait Exchange Foundation, died of acute myocardial infarction, acute cardiac failure complications, and septicemic shock, in the early morning of the 15th in Taipei. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> Sun Yun-suan was born November 11, 1913, in Penglai, Shandong, and graduated from the Electrical Engineering Department of Harbin Industrial University. </seg>
<seg id="4"> He was a member of the Tenth and Thirteenth Central Committees of the KMT, a member of the Eleventh and Twelfth Standing Central Committees, and a member of the Fourteenth Central Evaluation Committee, the Chair of the Presidium of the Central Evaluation Committee, and a member of the Fifteenth Central Evaluation Committee. </seg>
<seg id="5"> He took positions including "Transportation Minister," "Economic Minister," and "Premier of the Executive Yuan," etc. of the Taiwanese authorities. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060215.0060" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> Heilongjiang Develops Assessment and Strategy Projects for Water Pollution Impacts of Songhua River on Ecological Environment </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, February 16 (reporter: Hu Tao). To do a good job with the subsequent monitoring, pollution prevention and control work during the Songhua River's frozen and low water and ice-melting periods, Heilongjiang Province will actively implement assessment and strategy projects for the water pollution impact of Songhua River on the ecological environment. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> The reporter learned from the Environmental Protection Bureau of Heilongjiang Province that the Assessment and Strategy Projects for the Impacts of the Songhua River Big Pollution Accident on the Ecological Environment organized and led by the State's Environmental Protection Bureau have determined 15 specialized subjects that are divided into five aspects, including emergent environmental assessment and strategy, ecological effect assessment and human health, pollution control projects, comprehensive assessment, and technological concentration, and they are scheduled and arranged to be completed in three phases. </seg>
<seg id="4"> Currently, there are a total of 10 scientific research institutes and colleges and more than 60 individuals who have assumed technological research work on the 14 subjects. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5"> As it is presented, environmental protection departments and related scientific research organizations will regard the five subjects as emergent environmental assessment and strategy ones, and make every effort to solve the environmental problems the masses are most concerned by, </seg>
<seg id="6"> which include the concentration of featured pollutants in the main control section and predictions of the total escape amount; assessment of the pollution impacts on the safety of aquatic products from the Songhua River; assessment of the impacts on the safety of randomly obtaining water along both banks of the river and the underground water supply; a study on a plan of emergent purification technology for secure urban water supplies; and a study on the regularity of pollutant residues and their melting away in the frozing and melting processes of the Songhua River. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> The environmental protection departments of Heilongjiang Province will also further strengthen environmental supervision and investigation along the banks of the Songhua River, and strictly investigate and punish activities of illegally discharging pollutants and constructions that cause serious pollution. </seg>
<seg id="8"> Heilongjiang will send environmental law enforcement workers to urge and guide locals to conduct small-river basin environmental control, and perfect the environmental control system for branches such as the Ashi River, the Hulan River, and the Tangwang River, etc. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060215.0085" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> Peking University Sets Up Mourning Hall to Express Condolences over Academician Wang Xuan </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 15 (reporter: Li Jiangtao). Through several days of tense arrangements, the mourning hall for Academician Wang Xuan that was set up at the Memorial of the Hundred-Year Anniversary of Peking University was formally opened at 9 a.m. on the morning of the 15th. By noon of that day, several hundred people had come and offered their condolences. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> Before the mourning hall's opening time, about 8 a.m. that morning, several dozen people had waited in a long line outside the hall's gate. </seg>
<seg id="4"> Inside the memorial hall, the reporter saw the dark, horizontal banner with the calligraphy "Express Profound Condolences over Academician Wang Xuan" hanging on the wall of the Memorial of the Hundred-Year Anniversary of Peking University. </seg>
<seg id="5"> Below the banner, there was a big picture of Wang Xuan that was more than ten square meters in size. Wang was wearing a pair of glasses, smiling with a scholarly air. </seg>
<seg id="6"> Several cypress trees and several dozen wreaths were put along both sides of the picture. </seg>
<seg id="7"> An elegiac couplet on a wreath was written like this: "It began in the Qin Dynasty, prospered in the Tang Dynasty, glorified China, and skillfully laid a foundation; the contemporary Bi Sheng said farewell to the lead age, greeted the electronic one, and drew a blueprint." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="8"> Low-volume funeral music was mingled in the mourning hall, in a solemn and respectful atmosphere. </seg>
<seg id="9"> Among groups who came to express their condolences, there were leaders, teachers, students of Peking University, and friends, colleagues, students, neighbors of Academician Wang Xuan, and also, many strangers who did not know him. </seg>
<seg id="10"> Some of them held fresh flowers in their hands; some carried flower baskets; everybody, wearing small white flowers on their chests, slowly walked to the picture of Academician Wang Xuan, and bowed to express their condolences. </seg>
<seg id="11"> Many could not help but weep warm tears. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="12"> Zhang Wenbin, who was the Director of the State's Cultural Relic Bureau and an old alumnus of Peking University, told the reporter that, more than ten years ago, when he worked in Henan Province, he invited Professor Wang Xuan to give a report on scientific and technological innovation for cadres of the provincial Party Committee. </seg>
<seg id="13"> "The conduct and academic studies of Academician Wang Xuan are the model for us to learn. He made important contributions for the country and society, and people will never forget him." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="14"> Jin Ruilin, a professor at Peking University's Law School, has been an old friend and neighbor of Wang Xuan for more than 40 years. </seg>
<seg id="15"> He just left the hospital several days ago, and insisted on coming today to say farewell to his old friend. </seg>
<seg id="16"> When Mr. Jin wrote his words in the visitors' book, he could not help but sadden and wipe the tears pouring from his eyes many times with tissues. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="17"> He told the reporter that Professor Wang Xuan lived a very simple life, "when he lived in Tongfu Yuan, he had already been a professor and had accomplished significant achievements. But he still lived in a very small one-level house for many years. </seg>
<seg id="18"> He later moved to Chengze Yuan, where he had a space of 70 to 80 square meters, and lived there for more than ten years. </seg>
<seg id="19"> He refused an offer when Peking University provided him a big 140-square-meter flat in the Academician Building located in Lan Qiying; he also refused an upper-floor flat provided by Fangzheng Building. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="20"> Mr. Jin recalled and said with deep emotion that when Wang Xuan visited foreign countries, he simply refused to take positions with very good offers provided by foreign institutions. </seg>
<seg id="21"> "He insisted on not applying for the title of Academician at the beginning; then he gave up and filled out an application only after Mr. Zhou Peiyuan went to get him moving him many times." </seg>
<seg id="22"> Another thing that moved Mr. Jin was Wang Xuan's attitude toward the training of young people, "he himself stressed many times that what should be found and relied on are not what achievements I have achieved, not myself, but the training of young people." </seg>
<seg id="23"> Mr. Jin said that when Wang Xuan was around more than 50 years old, he started to pay attention to cultivating young people. He had stressed that we should pave a path, be willing to become a human ladder, and make way for young people. </seg>
<seg id="24"> "It is not easy at all for a very accomplished scientist to do this." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="25"> The reporter learned from the Peking University news center that the mourning hall for Academician Wang Xuan will open to the public for people coming from various circles to express their condolences from 9 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. every day from 9 a.m. on February 15 to 12:00 noon on February 19. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="26"> Professor Wang Xuan of Peking University died from a disease after the failure of a medical treatment at 11:03 p.m. on February 13 at Beijing Xiehe Hospital. He was 70 years old. He was praised as a "Contemporary Bi Sheng," and had assumed positions including Vice-Chair of the National Political Consultation Conference, Academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, Academician of the Chinese Engineering Academy, and Academician of the Third World's Academy of Sciences. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060215.0181" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> (Foreign Affairs) China's National People's Congress Establishes Exchange Mechanism with Chilean Parliament </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Wu Bangguo Attended the Signature Ceremony and Signed the Agreement </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 15 (reporter: Rong Yan). President of the National People's Congress Wu Bangguo attended the signature ceremony for a political dialogue and relation agreement established between China's National People's Congress and the Chilean Parliament, and signed the agreement document on the 15th. </seg>
<seg id="4"> The exchange mechanism between China's National Congress and the Chilean Parliament has been formally established. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5"> As it has been learned, Senate President of the Chilean Parliament Romero and President of the Chamber of Deputies Asensio had signed the agreement a few days ago in the Chilean capital of Santiago. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="6"> According to the agreement, both sides will follow the principles determined by the communique on the establishment of diplomatic relations between China and Chile, establish a political dialogue relation between China's National People's Congress and Chile's Parliament, set up a dialogue committee, hold irregular meetings in turn in the two countries, and jointly promote thorough development of relations between the two countries. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> Ambassador of the Chilean Embassy in China Cabrera and others attended the signature ceremony. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060215.0253" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> China to Implement Protection Regulation on Dissemination Rights for Information Networks </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 15 (reporters: Zhou Wei and Li Fei). Many networks and websites currently rely on republishing a lot of news and reports from newspapers and magazines to increase their click rates, but many of them are neither authorized, nor pay related fees. To cope with this, Director of the Copyright Department of the State Copyright Bureau Wang Ziqiang said in a press conference, held by the News Office of the State Council on the 15th, that the State Council will explain about the implementation of the Protection Regulation on Dissemination Rights for Information Networks, on the issue of paying for republishing works on the Internet. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> Wang Ziqiang said that according to existing laws and regulations, regarding those works published in newspapers, as long as their authors did not state that "they cannot be used," newspapers can use those works without their authors' permission, but at the same time should pay them, and the State Copyright Bureau has made the payment standard specifically for newspaper reprint practices according to the law. </seg>
<seg id="4"> However, according to regulations in existing laws, newspapers have the right to such legal permissions, but the Internet currently does not have rights for such legal permissions. </seg>
<seg id="5"> According to related interpretations made by the People's Supreme Court, the legal permission for newspaper reprints is applied to the Internet, i.e. to any small or short articles published in newspapers or on the Internet, whose authors did not state that "they cannot be used," the Internet can use them without permission, but at the same time needs to pay their authors. </seg>
<seg id="6"> But because the legal interpretation does not determine the payment standard, the Internet has not made payments when it used those works in practice. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> "Regarding whether the Internet use of published small or short works applies to the legal permission, it still needs to be determined according to the laws." </seg>
<seg id="8"> Wang Ziqiang said: "Whether it will be included in a category of law depends on the confirmation of the implementation of the Protection Regulation on Dissemination Rights for Information Networks this year." </seg>
</p>
</doc>
