<p>
<seg id="1"> (International) Russian Military Says Georgian Parliament's Resolution Will Not Affect Russia's Peacekeeping Activities </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Moscow, February 15 (reporter: Song Shiyi). Xie Duofu, a news officer for the Russian Defense Ministry, told the media on the 15th that the resolution made by the Georgian Parliament on Russia's peacekeeping troops will not affect the Russian military's peacekeeping activities in the short term, and Russian troops will continue to fulfill their peacekeeping mission in the conflict area of South Ossetia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> The Chair of the Russian Independent State Affairs Committee of the State Duma (lower house of the parliament), Kokoshin, made a speech and indicated regarding the resolution made by the Georgian Parliament on Russia's peacekeeping troops, on the same day the resolution was published, that the resolution will harm the stability of the situation in that area and negatively impact the relations between Russia and Georgia. </seg>
<seg id="4"> He stressed that the resolution made by the Georgian Parliament is a further bad step toward damaging the relations between Russia and Georgia. </seg>
<seg id="5"> He thinks that the Georgian accusation against the Russian side is absurd. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="6"> The Georgian Parliament passed the resolution on that day, and requested Russia's peacekeeping troops to stop their peacekeeping activities in South Ossetia, but did not set a concrete deadline for Russia's peacekeeping troops to withdraw. </seg>
<seg id="7"> The Georgian Parliament accuses Russia's peacekeeping personnel of a failure to fulfill their designated obligation, and regards the actions taken by Russia in the conflict area as "trying to annex Georgian territory." </seg>
<seg id="8"> The Georgian Parliament requests the Georgian government to take an active action and consider inviting international peacekeeping troops - to be stationed in the conflict area of South Ossetia - to replace the peacekeeping activities currently undertaken by Russia in that area. </seg>
<seg id="9"> The Georgian Parliament also requests the government to revise a related agreement that determined the stationing of Russia's peacekeeping personnel in the conflict area. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="10"> South Ossetia is an autonomous Georgian state, and borders with Russia's Republic of North Ossetia. </seg>
<seg id="11"> It announced its own independence after the Soviet Union collapsed, and has been confronting Georgia's central government for a long time. </seg>
<seg id="12"> Russia currently has a peacekeeping battalion of 500 soldiers stationed in that area. </seg>
<seg id="13"> The troops stationed there are based on the agreement signed by four parties - including Russia, Georgia, North Ossetia, and South Ossetia - in 1992. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060216.0007" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> Large Fire Occurs at Liaoyuan Hospital; Four Individuals Responsible to be Prosecuted as Liable for Big Accident as Suspects </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Changchun, February 16 (reporter: Zhou Liquan). After the large fire disaster occurred at the Central Hospital of Liaoyuan City in Jilin Province, an accident investigation group determined that 11 individuals are responsible, and among them, the head of the electrician team of the hospital, Zhang Diankun, and three other persons will be prosecuted as liable for the big accident. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> The Central Hospital, the largest one in Liaoyuan City, experienced a big fire on December 15, 2005, which eventually took 39 lives. </seg>
<seg id="4"> The total burned area in this fire disaster was more than 5,000 square meters. </seg>
<seg id="5"> As it has been learned, this is the biggest fire accident in the national medical and health system since New China was established. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="6"> As was investigated, at around 16:30 on the day the accident occurred, there was a sudden power failure at the Central Hospital of Liaoyuan City. Based on the hospital's electrical circuit design, if there is a power failure, the circuit breaker in the transformer box should automatically switch to a backup socket to maintain normal power supply for the hospital. But at that time the circuit breaker did not automatically switch to the socket. Zhang Diankun, the head of the technician team, forced the power supply without investigating and clarifying the cause of the power failure, and caused the fire disaster. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> Those smoky underground cables, which should be laid out on a flat surface in very good order, were tangled together without any order, and fire prevention layers should be set up. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="8"> Thus, three individuals including Zhao Yongchun, the 57-year-old head of the electrical equipment installation team of the Textile Company of Liaoyuan City, Sun Fenglin, a retired cadre (senior engineer) from the Liaoyuan Power Affairs Bureau, and Jin Taicheng, a reemployed retiree worker at the Central Hospital of Liaoyuan City, will be prosecuted as suspects in the liability for the big accident. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060216.0024" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> First Tourism Ceremony in Guizhou for China's Rural Village Tourism Held in Tianlong Tunbao </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Guiyang, February 16 (reporter: Shi Xinrong). On the morning of the 16th, adults and children were all wearing their festive costumes together and smiling cheerfully in Tianlong Village, Tianlong Towship, Pingba County, Guizhou Province. </seg>
<seg id="3"> At 10:30 a.m., after the Five-Grain Sacrifice to the Year activity had ended, Zheng Peiqin, an 80-year-old villager wearing a long-sleeved, light green gown, first banged the gong for the First Tourism Ceremony of China's Rural Village Tourism in Guizhou. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> Tianlong Tunbao Village is a typical representative of rural village tourism development in Guizhou, and a display model of national rural village tourism. </seg>
<seg id="5"> The "Tunbao People" have a history of more than 600 years as the descendents of those stationed troops who were sent there during the Hongwu Period of the Ming Dynasty. </seg>
<seg id="6"> Locals wearing blue gowns with wide belts and sleeves can be found everywhere here. The ancient Han culture and clothes are maintained very well in Tunbao Village. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7"> As has been learned, based on the advantage of cultural tradition, Tianlong Village has been developing rural village cultural tourism since 2002, and the ticket income for entrances alone was 3.8 million Yuan in 2005. More than 47% of farmer households have participated in the tourist business through food and restaurant, transportation, sale of tourist merchandise, etc. Farmers' income per capita has increased from 1,300 Yuan in 2002 to 2,640 Yuan in 2005. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="8"> As Director of the Tourism Bureau of Guizhou Province Yang Shengming stated, after the first tourism ceremony in Tianlong Tunbao, 35 tourism projects will be developed for rural village tourism activities in Guizhou under the theme of "new countryside, new tourism, new experience, and new trend." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="9"> More than 130 villages have developed various rural village tourism projects in Guizhou so far, and more than 600,000 farming households had been lifted from poverty through tourism development in the entire province by 2005. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060216.0036" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> Housing Prices Increased 5.5% in 70 Cities Nationwide; Housing Prices in Shanghai Continued to Fall in January </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 16 (reporter: Liu Zhen). In January of this year, housing prices increased 5.5% in 70 large and medium cities nationwide compared with that of last year, and the rate of price increases fell 0.7% compared with that of last month. </seg>
<seg id="3"> Housing prices in Shanghai continued to fall. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> The data published by the State's Development and Reform Committee and the State's Statistics Bureau on the 16th demonstrate that among 70 large and medium cities, most housing sales prices increased on the average by a small margin in January of this year compared with that of last year. The rate of housing price increases was more than 10% in Hohhot and Dalian; however, housing sale prices in Shanghai continued to fall by a small margin, falling 0.4% compared with last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5"> The statistics in the same way demonstrate that the housing sales prices in Shanghai increased 19.1% in the first season of last year, compared with that of the year before last year. The trend changed after that. Since the second half of last year, the price has demonstrated a downward trend by a small margin, compared with that of the year before last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="6"> In January of this year, the sale price of newly built commercial housing in 70 large and medium cities increased 6.9% compared with that of last year, and the rate of price increases fell 0.2% compared with that of last month. </seg>
<seg id="7"> Cities that experienced higher rates of increase in sale prices for newly built commercial housing compared with that of last year include 18.9% in Dalian, 14.7% in Hohhot, 10.0% in Shenzhen, 9.1% in Chengdu, 8.4% in Beijing; but the increased price rate in Shanghai fell 3.1% compared with that of last year. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060216.0088" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> Central Organization Department of CCP Requires Further Strengthening of Supervision Work for Selection and Appointment of Leaders and Cadres </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 16. The Central Organization Department recently printed and issued a suggestion regarding strengthening the supervision work for cadres. </seg>
<seg id="3"> The suggestion requires that Party organization departments at every level should strictly control, care for, and protect cadres, and conduct supervision work for cadres at every stage of cadres' cultivation and education, review and test, selection and appointment, and routine management, and establish, perfect, and strengthen prevention work, promptly discover problems in the supervision work mechanism, seriously correct them, and truly strengthen the supervision work for selection and appointment of leaders and cadres. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> The suggestion points out that the primary tasks of the organization departments for cadre supervision include, first, supervision of the leadership team and leaders, and its priority is to strengthen supervision of the major leader of a leadership team; second, supervision of the selection and appointment work of leaders of the Party and administrations, and its priority is to supervise and review implementation of the Working Regulation on Selection and Appointment of leaders of the Party and Administrations. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5"> With regards to the supervision of the leadership team and leaders, the suggestion proposes that the ideal and good-faith education and anti-corruption and honesty promotion education should be consistently adhered to, and those educations should be practiced in cultivation, selection, control, and supervision of cadres, guide and urge leaders to strengthen their training of the Party spirit, and stick to strengthening the ideological and ethical frontline, emphasizing that the Party is established for the public, the administration is for the people, and anti-corruption is to prevent degeneration. </seg>
<seg id="6"> Honesty and self-discipline should clearly come up as requirements when talking with newly promoted cadres in their appointment meetings. </seg>
<seg id="7"> Leadership teams at every level should be urged to stick to the democratic centralization system, establish and perfect rules and procedures for meetings and decision-making, and carefully practice the system that integrates collective leadership with individual responsibility in related fields. </seg>
<seg id="8"> The supervision over the major leader of a leadership team should be emphasized. Leaders of organization (personnel) departments should frequently talk with and conduct heart-to-heart talks with the major leader of a leadership team at the next lower level to learn the status of his ideology, work, and style of work, etc. </seg>
<seg id="9"> A routine control and supervision system should be established and perfected for leaders; the status of ideology and style of work of a leadership team should be regularly learned and analyzed, and suggestions and measures should be come up with to solve problems. </seg>
<seg id="10"> A warning talk and letter inquiry system for leaders should be practiced. Once the hint of a problem emerges, a warning talk or letter inquiry should be promptly conducted. </seg>
<seg id="11"> As for those obvious problems with leaders reported by the masses, they should be carefully investigated and clarified; if a problem is true, the leader concerned should be criticized and educated, or disciplined by appropriate organizational measures; if any leader violates any regulation or law, he or she should be transferred to the law or discipline enforcement organization to be investigated; if a leader is found innocent through an investigation, a clarification should be addressed for him or her in a proper manner. </seg>
<seg id="12"> At the same time, strengthening supervision of cadres should be integrated by encouraging cadres to boldly explore and develop innovations, and excellent cadres should be discovered and promptly commended. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="13"> The Suggestion requires that organization (personnel) departments at every level should truly strengthen the supervision work of selection and appointment of leaders of the Party and administrations. </seg>
<seg id="14"> Supervision measures on the stages of cadres' recommendation, nomination, test and review, discussion, and determination, etc., should be further perfected, and cadres should be strictly selected and used, and vigorous support should be provided for recommendation and selection of cadres who are politically reliable, talented at their work, maintain a good style of work, and are trusted by the masses of people to take leadership positions at every level. </seg>
<seg id="15"> The implementation status of the regulations for cadre appointment should be reviewed vigorously. Any conduct that violates the regulations for cadre appointment should be seriously investigated and disciplined, and indecent practices and corruption in the use of cadres should be firmly contained. </seg>
<seg id="16"> A supervision and investigation system for any serious violation of regulations for the use of cadres should be practiced to further strengthen supervision, investigation, and disciplinary work. </seg>
<seg id="17"> A system of selection and appointment of cadres - and investigation of their working responsibility - should be established and perfected. Based on the principle that power matches responsibility, every stage of the cadres' selection and appointment work, including the main body of responsibility and content of responsibility, should be scientifically defined, and an investigation method should be clarified to strengthen investigation work. </seg>
<seg id="18"> The supervision role played by the masses should be fully exercised to establish and perfect a reporting mechanism that is "convenient, secure, and highly efficient." </seg>
<seg id="19"> The supervision role played by public opinion should be fully employed, and the status of cadres' selection and appointment work should be notified to the news media within an appropriate amount of time, and accept the supervision of public opinion. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="20"> The suggestion proposes that a coordination mechanism of cadre supervision work should be further perfected. </seg>
<seg id="21"> Organization (personnel) departments should strengthen coordination with discipline investigation organizations, establish a work communication system, contact person system, and responsibility system, with discipline investigation organizations in the aspect of cadres' fair administration and their Party spirit, in order to strengthen integrated supervision. </seg>
<seg id="22"> Visiting and investigation work should be carefully and well done with discipline investigation organizations; visiting and investigating methods can be improved and perfected to promote visiting and investigation quality. </seg>
<seg id="23"> An auditing system for leaders' economic responsibility should be carefully practiced with auditing organizations. </seg>
<seg id="24"> An internal supervision mechanism for cadres' selection and appointment work of the organization departments should be perfected. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
<doc docid="XIN_CMN_20060216.0124" genre="newswire" sysid="chg">
<p>
<seg id="1"> (Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan) Taiwan Authorities Heavily Fine Leading High-Tech Enterprise for Violation of Regulation and Investment on Mainland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="2"> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, February 16 (reporter: Chen Jianxing). On the 15th, an economic affairs administration of the Taiwan authorities decided to fine Lianhua Electronics Corporation (shortened name: "Liandian"), one of "the two giant wafer producers" in Taiwan, 5 million New Taiwan Dollars, because it "violates regulation by providing assistance and participating in creation" for Hejian Science and Technology Company on the Mainland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3"> Taiwan's China Times reported that this is the first case used by Taiwanese authorities to fine and discipline a Taiwanese business that invested on the Mainland since Chen Shui-bian came up with the economic and trade policy of "actively controlling and effectively opening." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4"> As has been reported, a person from the Taiwan "Report and Review Committee of the Economic Department" said that the reason why Liandian was fined was because it violated "the Regulation of the People's Relation across the Strait," and regulations of "Permission Methods for Investment and Technological Cooperation on the Mainland." </seg>
<seg id="5"> In the future, the Report and Review Committee will fine Tsao Hsing-cheng, former Chair of the Board of Liandian, according to the circumstances. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="6"> The "Liandian Case" originated in February 2005, and by then Taiwanese investigation departments had used around a hundred people to hurriedly search the residences and offices of several high-level Liandian employees, and alleged that Liandian was suspected of investing on the Mainland and "illegally providing capital, technology, and human resources" to Hejian Science and Technology Company. </seg>
<seg id="7"> Tsao Hsing-cheng, the then-Chair of the Liandian Board, later publicly stated that Liandian did not violate any of the Taiwan authorities' regulations, and the assistance Liandian provided to Hejian Science and Technology was for Liandian's long-term interest, and Liandian would lose business opportunities if it did not enter the Mainland market as soon as possible. </seg>
<seg id="8"> After that, the "Financial Supervision and Control Committee" of the Taiwan authorities fined Liandian 3 million New Taiwan Dollars for its violation of the regulation regarding disclosure of commercial information. </seg>
<seg id="9"> On January 9, 2006, the Liandian Board accepted Tsao Hsing-cheng's resignation, and he was formally prosecuted for violation of regulations on investment on the Mainland within several hours. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="10"> Liandian and Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (shortened name: TSMC) are called "the two giant wafer producers" in Taiwan, and both are leading high-tech enterprises on the island. </seg>
<seg id="11"> A series of investigations and disciplinary actions taken by the Taiwan authorities against Liandian have attracted close attention from various circles on the island. </seg>
</p>
</doc>
