<seg id="15"> After price adjustments, the October-December quarter had a real increase of 1.4% over the previous quarter, a rate of increase higher than the expected 1.2%. </seg>
<seg id="16"> The main factors were strong domestic demand and growth in exports to major countries such as China and the US, indicating signs of sustained economic recovery. </seg>
