<seg id="1"> The Indian border paramilitary beefed up patrols at the Nepali borders on February 17. </seg>
<seg id="2"> Worrying that the upsurge in Maoists rebellions in recent months may infiltrate the border, the Sashastra Seema Bal (SSB), responsible for guarding the 200-mile stretch of India-Nepali border in the Darjeeling district, has increased three battalions. </seg>
<seg id="3"> Nepal borders at the Himalayas in the north. </seg>
<seg id="4"> Its other three sides border on India, with a 1,477-kilometer border. </seg>
<seg id="5"> Maoist insurgents frequently sneak into Indian border villages and obtain weapons from local gangs and drug dealers. </seg>
