<seg id="60"> An engineer was unfortunately shot to death when the Pakistani troops later rescued the hostages. </seg>
<seg id="61"> However, the kidnapping was believed to have been orchestrated by a militant group linked to al-Qaeda, and not by separatist insurgents. </seg>
<seg id="62"> Due to the frequent economic contacts between China and Pakistan, many Chinese engineers take part in Pakistani infrastructure projects and work in the local areas. </seg>
<seg id="63"> Tribal insurgents in Pakistan also accuse the government of seizing their natural resources. </seg>
<seg id="64"> As a result, Chinese have fallen victim to several attacks and kidnaps. </seg>
<seg id="65"> This is a news roundup by Phoenix TV. </seg>
</doc>
