<doc docid="CCTV4_NEWS3_CMN_20060217_075800_447_833.qrtr" genre="broadcast_news" sysid="chh">
<seg id="1"> The remains of three Chinese engineers killed in an attack in Pakistan left Karachi at 7 p.m. local time today to be repatriated on a special flight by the Pakistani air force. </seg>
<seg id="2"> Let's watch a report by this station's reporter in Pakistan, Tao Ye. </seg>
<seg id="3"> The remains of the three Chinese engineers killed on the 15th near Karachi in Pakistan were repatriated early on the 17th from Faisal Air Force Base in Karachi, Pakistan. </seg>
<seg id="4"> At first light, the atmosphere at Karachi's Faisal Air Force Base was solemn. </seg>
<seg id="5"> Chinese Ambassador to Pakistan Zhang Chunxiang, the minister of the interior of Sindh province, in which Karachi is located, and Chinese Consul-General in Pakistan Sun Chunye led Chinese embassy and consular employees in Pakistan and employees from Chinese companies in bidding a final farewell to their fallen compatriots. </seg>
