<seg id="1"> <HEADLINE> The Incorporation of Batey Ads into JWT's Network: Is It Too Late to Say Happy New Year? </seg>
</hl>
<poster>
<seg id="2"> <POSTER>  BrandVista Post: </seg>
</poster>
<seg id="3"> Hello, everybody. </seg>
<seg id="4"> Once again, the Chinese New Year has flown by and those who combined their vacation time with their New Year's holiday are now returning to their jobs. </seg>
<seg id="5"> We wish all our friends a happy New Year, if it is not too late to say Happy New Year. </seg>
<seg id="6"> We spoke recently at a cafe with NPLCN. He talked about present-day Brandvista. </seg>
<seg id="7"> The appearance of the website has improved greatly. </seg>
<seg id="8"> The content is well structured. </seg>
<seg id="9"> What pleases him most is the Discuz-powered community BBS, which has undergone a thorough revamping. </seg>
<seg id="10"> In regards to the community, I must thank one person. </seg>
<seg id="11"> That is, Mr. Li Mingshun, general manager of Discuz Beijing. </seg>
<seg id="12"> If you search for his name in Google, you will get a slew of hits. </seg>
<seg id="13"> You probably know that he was previously with Sina. He later started his own business, setting up an Internet advertisement exchange platform for SMEs that was similar to the overseas website Adbrite.com. </seg>
<seg id="14"> We discussed it with him at the time on MSN. What he said, in general, was that: Brandvista felt that the development of many industries in China depended on the expansion of the private economy and SMEs. </seg>
<seg id="15"> And currently, in the Chinese market, this situation does not give reason for optimism. </seg>
<seg id="16"> So SME's in creative industries and similar services are unable to provide consultation to any significant extent. </seg>
<seg id="17"> Collecting high fees to advance one's own development in the end leads to a discouraging cycle. </seg>
<seg id="18"> Later, he came to Discuz. </seg>
<seg id="19"> Discuz is an outstanding forum program powered by PHP and MySQL. </seg>
<seg id="20"> With the help of Ramboo, a technical engineer from Beijing, Brandvista finally saw the light of day once again and hit the stage with matchless freshness. </seg>
<seg id="21"> The feedback was very good. </seg>
<seg id="22"> The interface was neat and friendly. </seg>
<seg id="23"> It was also very fast. </seg>
<seg id="24"> With the neat interface, writing a few words that moved me and inspired others, exchanging tidbits about work and life with friends from the same industry that shared the same pursuits, I began to find that this was a pleasure. </seg>
<seg id="25"> Thank you Discuz! </seg>
<seg id="26"> Recently, there has been a lot of news from the advertising industry. </seg>
<seg id="27"> Starting in January, the WTO system of openness in the ad industry began to be implemented. </seg>
<seg id="28"> Large foreign companies have been arriving one after another. Small foreign companies are sharpening their sword for battle. It seems to be a scene of prosperity. </seg>
<seg id="29"> Batey Ads, which rose to prominence in Singapore, has been having many difficulties. </seg>
<seg id="30"> Having lost a string of big clients and having suffered repeated setbacks in its development in mainland China, Martin Boase finally took a little time from a lawsuit in Italy to think about shuffling things around. </seg>
<seg id="31"> Batey Ads will merge into JWT's network, keeping its own brandname and being managed by JWT. </seg>
<seg id="32"> However, at the same time, there were also rumors that Bates and 141 Network would merge into the Ogilvy and Mather system and be managed by the Ogilvy and Mather network. </seg>
<seg id="33"> Even if 141 had already given its report to Ogilvy and Mather prior to that, having Ted Bates get payback against Ogilvy and Mather is also a interesting matter. </seg>
